net.hudup.core.data

Class AttributeList

  • java.lang.Object
    • net.hudup.core.data.AttributeList
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.io.Serializable, java.lang.Cloneable, TextParsable, Transfer

    public class AttributeList
extends java.lang.Object
implements Cloneable, TextParsable, java.io.Serializable, Transfer
    This class represents a list of attribute, called attribute list, as a convention. It has a built-in variable list containing all attribute. It provides utility methods processing such list (adding an element, setting an element, removing an element, etc.) as the Java List and more advanced methods. Recall that attribute represented by Attribute class indicates the data type, which is also a wrapper of data type. Profile is one of important data structures, like record of table in database, has a list of values. Each value belongs to a particular attribute. Profile uses attribute to specify its data types and so profile owns a reference to an attribute list. In general, attribute list is very important to profile.
    Version:
    10.0
    Author:
    Loc Nguyen

      • nomalizeId

        public AttributeList nomalizeId(java.lang.String idName,
                                Attribute.Type type,
                                boolean autoInc)
        Normalizing this attribute list. In current implementation, this method only set the identification (ID) attribute of this attribute list is key and auto-increment (according to the parameter autoInc) attribute. The ID attribute is established according to input parameters such as idName, type, and autoInc.
        Parameters:
        idName - Name of identification (ID) attribute.
        type - Type of identification (ID) attribute.
        autoInc - Whether or not the identification (ID) attribute has auto-increment mechanism.
        Returns:
        AttributeList

      • getKeys

        public Keys getKeys()
        Recall that Profile is one of important data structures, like record of table in database, has a list of values. Each value belongs to a particular attribute. In a profile, a key attribute or a set of some key attributes are used to distinguish two profiles. If there is only one key attribute, we state that the profile has single key. A integer single key is also called identification (ID). If there are a set of key attributes, we state that the profile has complex key. Single key and complex key are represented by the Keys class. This method returns a list of key attribute in this attribute list represented by Keys class. Note that the method Attribute.isKey() of a key attribute returns true.
        Returns:
        Keys of attribute list

      • getEmptyKeyCondition

        public Condition getEmptyKeyCondition()
        Recall that Profile is one of important data structures, like record of table in database, has a list of values. Each value belongs to a particular attribute. In a profile, a key attribute or a set of some key attributes are used to distinguish two profiles. If there is only one key attribute, we state that the profile has single key. A integer single key is also called identification (ID). If there are a set of key attributes, we state that the profile has complex key. Single key and complex key are represented by the Keys class. Condition is the special profile which is used in condition clause where in SQL statement for processing database, for example. However condition can be used in any necessary situation. This method creates an empty condition of key attributes. All values of empty condition are null.
        Returns:
        Empty condition of key attributes.

      • defaultAttributeMapAttributeList

        public static AttributeList defaultAttributeMapAttributeList()
        Creating the default attribute list of attribute map. Attribute map is used to mapping additional internal information to external information. For example, given the internal table Item in Hudup database contains only item identification (item ID) and item name. There is an external table Product in outside database contains product price and product vendor. The attribute map allows to mapping product price and product vendor into Hudup database as item price and item vendor. Such attribute list has three attributes whose names are specified by constants as follows:
        • DataConfig.INTERNAL_UNIT_FIELD, for example, the internal table "Item" in Hudup database.
        • DataConfig.INTERNAL_ATTRIBUTE_NAME_FIELD, for example, the field "item price" in Hudup database.
        • DataConfig.INTERNAL_ATTRIBUTE_VALUE_FIELD, for example, the value field "12 USD" in Hudup database.
        • DataConfig.EXTERNAL_UNIT_FIELD, for example, the external table "Product" in outside database.
        • DataConfig.EXTERNAL_ATTRIBUTE_NAME_FIELD, for example, the field "product price" in outside database.
        • DataConfig.EXTERNAL_ATTRIBUTE_VALUE_FIELD, for example, the value field "10 Euro" in outside database.
        Returns:
        Default attribute list of attribute map. Such attribute list forms a structure of a attribute map storage such as a table of attribute map in database.

      • defaultContextTemplateAttributeList

        public static AttributeList defaultContextTemplateAttributeList()
        Creating the default attribute list of context template. ContextTemplate is template for a context represented by the class Context. Context includes time, location, companion, etc. associated with a user when she/he is buying, studying, etc. Such attribute list has four attributes whose names are specified by constants as follows:
        • DataConfig.CTX_TEMPLATEID_FIELD
        • DataConfig.CTX_NAME_FIELD
        • DataConfig.CTX_TYPE_FIELD
        • DataConfig.CTX_PARENT_FIELD
        Returns:
        Default attribute list of context template. Such attribute list forms a structure of a context template storage such as a table of context template in database.
